  <fr:p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a,a':A]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _\bullet \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}a = x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi '_\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}a'=x]]></fr:tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a,\chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 with 
 <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a',\chi '_\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, we employ the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0035.xml"
addr="erct-0035"
title="Covariant sum of a left-cloven family of path objects">covariant sum</fr:link> of each of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001C.xml"
addr="erct-001C"
title="Dependent product of path objects">pointwise path object</fr:link> structures on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}-=x]]></fr:tex> over the <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-0013.xml"
addr="erct-0013"
title="The intrinsic path object on a type">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, constructing an identification <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p\colon  a = a']]></fr:tex> followed by a homotopy <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H \colon    \mathopen {}\left \lparen   \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {} _*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}  \sim  \chi '_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[z\colon  A]]></fr:tex>, we compute:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \begin {aligned}         \mathopen {}\left \lparen   \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {} _*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\textstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{  \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {} }}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}  z       &=         \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {} _*^{-=z} \chi _z       \\       &=       \chi _{a'}^{-1} \cdot  \chi _z       \\       &= \chi '_z     \end {aligned}   ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="erct-001J.xml"
addr="erct-001J"
title="Sets">set</fr:link>, which we may deduce from <fr:ref
addr="erct-001K"
href="erct-001K.xml"
taxon="Lemma" /> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-001L"
href="erct-001L.xml"
taxon="Lemma" />.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
